The paper deals with face attribute prediction from face images, which is a computer vision problem. The use of deep learning networks, specifically CNNs, is a key aspect of the paper. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of off-the-shelf CNNs and their representations for facial feature extraction, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves classification, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The datasets used in the experiments are image datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the combination of traditional computer vision techniques with deep learning networks, which is a topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
